e":"Brussel, Brabant, België"},"en":{"environ 1090–":"about 1090–Deceased","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1080–1166":"1080–1166","1095–Female":"1095–Deceased","1090–Female":"1090–Deceased","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1166":"1166","environ 1095":"about 1095","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","environ 1090":"about 1090","Bruxelles, Brabant, Belgique":"Brussels, Brabant, Belgium","nameMeanings":[{"name":"MALLET","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Jean-Yves, Adelard, Alain, Henri, Jacques, Leonce, Lucien, Monique, Philippe.","French: nickname from a diminutive of   Mal   ‘bad’. Alternatively, from a derivative of the related Old French word <i>maleit</i> ‘accursed’ (from Latin <i>maledictus</i>, the opposite of <i>benedictus</i> ‘blessed’), applied as a nickname for an unlucky person. Compare   Malet   1.","French: variant of   Malet   2, an Old French pet form of the personal name   Malo  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Mallatt","meanings":["English: variant of   Mallet  ."]},{"name":"Mallette","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre, Donat, Emile, Francois, Jacques, Laurent, Pierre, Rolande.","Altered form of French   Mallet  , reflecting the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>. Compare   Mallett  .","English: rare variant of   Mallett  ."]},{"name":"Mal","meanings":["Slovenian: nickname for a physically small man, from <i>mal</i> ‘small, little’.","French (mainly Nord): nickname from <i>mal</i> ‘bad’ (from Latin <i>malus</i>).","Indian (northern states): variant of   Mall  ."]}]},{"name":"Béatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Béatrix MALLET was born about 1090. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Engelbert II D'ENGHIEN."},"et":{"environ 1090–":"umbes 1090–Surnud","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1080–1166":"1080–1166","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1166":"1166","environ 1095":"umbes 1095","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","environ 1090":"umbes 1090","Bruxelles, Brabant, Belgique":"Brussel, Brabant, Belgia"},"fi":{"environ 1090–":"noin 1090–Kuollut","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1080–1166":"1080–1166","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1090–Female":"1090–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1166":"1166","environ 1095":"noin 1095","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","environ 1090":"noin 1090","Bruxelles, Brabant, Belgique":"Brussel, Brabant, Belgia"},"fr":{"environ 1090–":"environ 1090–Décédée","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1080–1166":"1080–1166","1095–Female":"1095–Décédée","1090–Female":"1090–Décédée","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1166":"1166","environ 1095":"environ 1095","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","environ 1090":"environ 1090","Bruxelles, Brabant, Belgique":"Bruxelles, Brabant, Belgique","lifeSummary":"Béatrix MALLET est née environ 1090. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Engelbert II D'ENGHIEN."},"de":{"environ 1090–":"um 1090–Verstorben","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1080–1166":"1080–1166","1095–Female":"1095–Verstorben","1090–Female":"1090–Verstorben","1080":"1080","1090":"1090","1166":"1166","environ 1095":"um 1095","1130":"1130","1095":"1095","environ 1090":"um 1090","Bruxelles, Brabant, Belgique":"Brüssel, Brabant, Belgien","lifeSummary":"Béatrix MALLET wurde um 1090 geboren. Sie hatte mit Engelbert II D'ENGHIEN mindestens 1 Sohn 